Grenada first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Grenada had a population of 314. The population density was {{convert|608.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Grenada was 248 (79.0%) [[White Americans|White]], 5 (1.6%) [[African Americans|African American]], 10 (3.2%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 4 (1.3%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 9 (2.9%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 38 (12.1%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 24 persons (7.6%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Grenada CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0631246 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The census reported that 94.3% of the population lived in households and 5.7% were institutionalized.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 117 households, out of which 31 (26.5%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 55 (47.0%) were married-couple households, 12 (10.3%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 24 (20.5%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 26 (22.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 28 households (23.9%) were one person, and 16 (13.7%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.53.<ref name=DP1/> There were 77 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (65.8% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Grenada CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0631246 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 60 people (19.1%) under the age of 18, 26 people (8.3%) aged 18 to 24, 61 people (19.4%) aged 25 to 44, 70 people (22.3%) aged 45 to 64, and 97 people (30.9%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 48.8{{nbsp}}years.    For every 100 females, there were 112.2 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 122 housing units at an average density of {{convert|236.4|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 117 (95.9%) were occupied. Of these, 73 (62.4%) were owner-occupied, and 44 (37.6%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0631246|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715025240/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0631246|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Grenada CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Grenada had a population of 367. The population density was {{convert|709.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Grenada was 307 (83.7%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 2 (0.5%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 35 (9.5%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 1 (0.3%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 3 (0.8%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 19 (5.2%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 12 persons (3.3%).

The Census reported that 367 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 162 households, out of which 40 (24.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 60 (37.0%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 19 (11.7%) had a female householder with no husband present, 7 (4.3%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 9 (5.6%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 1 (0.6%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 58 households (35.8%) were made up of individuals, and 36 (22.2%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.27.  There were 86 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (53.1% of all households); the average family size was 3.06.

The population was spread out, with 81 people (22.1%) under the age of 18, 20 people (5.4%) aged 18 to 24, 85 people (23.2%) aged 25 to 44, 86 people (23.4%) aged 45 to 64, and 95 people (25.9%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 44.5 years. For every 100 females, there were 92.1 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 91.9 males.

There were 193 housing units at an average density of {{convert|373.3|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 80 (49.4%) were owner-occupied, and 82 (50.6%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 2.4%; the rental vacancy rate was 23.4%.  218 people (59.4% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 149 people (40.6%) lived in rental housing units.

